But you can't really enable those warnings if you want to use -Werr, right?<p>And I've always found the "always true/false due to limited range of data type" to be counterproductive. Something like<p><pre><code>    int i;
    ...
    assert(i <= SSIZE_MAX);
    f(i);
</code></pre>
can make sense, but will cause gcc to complain if int and ssize_t happen to be the same size.
